</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2 data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">What is MEXC?</span></h2>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC is a leading global cryptocurrency exchange for buying, selling, and trading digital assets. Founded by Ryder Junji and led by CEO John Chen, a Singaporean businessman, the company is headquartered in Victoria, Seychelles. Through the mexc app, the platform provides a range of services, with a core focus on spot and futures trading, leveraged exchange-traded funds (ETFs), perpetual futures, an NFT Index, and portfolio management.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">Beyond spot and futures trading, the mexc app also offers services like staking and airdrops to its over 40 million users worldwide. Banking professionals built the reliable trading engine, which handles 1.4 million transactions each second, ensuring high-speed performance. With low trading fees and multilingual support to enhance the user&#8217;s experience, the mexc app tends to every need, making it a favorite among experienced traders. User security is prioritized through a multi-tier, multi-cluster system architecture.</span></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193322 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/What-is-MEXC.jpg" alt="What is MEXC?" width="1363" height="628" /></span></strong></p>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">If you&#8217;re looking to diversify your portfolio further via spot and futures trading, MEXC has staking and earning services, a launchpad for new projects, and demo trading for newcomers. You can also join the vibrant mexc trader community directly through the mexc app or access futures and spot markets on the web. Additionally, developers can use MEXC&#8217;s API to integrate data directly into their applications.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC has earned multiple licenses, like an MSB license in the US, one from AUSTRAC in Australia, and an MTR license in Estonia. These allow users to download the mexc app and access exchange, wallet, and remittance services globally. In 2023, MEXC experienced regulatory hurdles, including warnings from the BCSC, FMA, and BaFin, and the revocation of its Estonian license in November 2023.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Pros of MEXC</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An extensive range of trading pairs and cryptocurrencies. More than 2,700 virtual currencies are exchanged, mostly in USDT-denominated pairs. New coins are introduced quickly thanks to the voting method for new listings.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The platform has clear and upfront fees based on the activity type, trading pair, user VIP level, and MX tokens held. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC offers 0% maker and 0.0% taker fees on spot; 0% maker and 0.01% taker fees on futures.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC also provides a large selection of tools. Both novice and seasoned traders can benefit from trading, spot trading, futures, and a number of other options.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">With yields of up to 100% APY, it enables users to generate passive income from crypto. Additionally, users can benefit from trading with up to 500x leverage on specific perpetual contracts</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The platform has an easy-to-use, multilingual interface that even beginners can use.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Cons of MEXC</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Customer Support Complaint: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">A lot of users indicate that while simple questions might be resolved in a timely manner, serious questions around withdrawals, frozen accounts, or risk-control investigations take considerable time and provide unclear, high level answers or seem to be redirected to other support channels. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Regulatory and Licensing Issues: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Unlike registered and regulated exchanges, MEXC might not provide the same level of protections, as the company does not have all of the necessary regulatory licenses in key jurisdictions and has received warnings for operating unregistered from authorities in Canada (particularly the British Columbia Securities Commission), Germany, and Austria.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Token Quality and Liquidity for New Listings: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC can have issues with lower-capped coins, new tokens means lower liquidity, slippage, difficulty in executing trades, and in some extreme cases coins getting delisted and suffering big price drops. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Fiat and Withdrawal Limitations: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">There is a limited number of supported fiat currencies, and a lot of withdrawal options are limited, especially to users who haven’t completed higher-tier KYC. Large withdrawal may trigger more verification or delays. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Risk Controls / Account Freezes: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some users have mentioned that their accounts or funds are sometimes frozen and flagged as having “abnormal activity” or “risk control” even when they believe that they have completed all the KYC and verification steps. Account freezes can last a long time and restrict users from making withdrawals</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>MEXC Review: Trading Tools</strong></h2>
<h3><strong>Spot Trading on MEXC </strong></h3>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">This refers to the buying and selling of cryptocurrencies for quick settlement. Spot trading on MEXC Global allows users to trade the most diverse range of cryptocurrency pairs, including majors such as BTC/USDT and ETH/USDT, as well as several altcoins. In contrast to derivatives and futures, the notion is that you immediately own the user assets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193321 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/MEXC-spot-trading.jpg" alt="MEXC Review Trading Tools" width="1363" height="631" /></span></p>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC is regarded as one of the biggest altcoin exchanges in the world, listing more than 3,000 coins. This places the exchange significantly ahead of many rivals, which is beneficial for new users, active traders, and professional traders wishing to diversify beyond Bitcoin and Ethereum. Users can also participate in the daily m day event to win airdrops.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC provides a professional-grade spot trading dashboard with an order book view with real-time buy/sell activity and advanced charting tools powered by TradingView for technical analysis. To ensure user safety, the exchange maintains full platform reserves, often referred to as reserve assets. Legitimate users who follow the user agreement can trade confidently, and customer support is available for any assistance. It also offers multiple order types, which include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Market orders which execute instant buy/sell at the best price. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Limit orders allows you to set your own price</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stop-limit/stop-market orders which helps in risk management. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Iceberg orders used to hide large trades to avoid slippage.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">One cancels the other serves experienced traders. You can place two orders at once with this type of order. All subsequent orders are nullified by the first one that is activated.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC also provides a number of technical indicators to help you determine whether to buy or sell. Popular tools include K-lines, moving averages, and MACD.</span></p>
<h3 data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">Perpetual Futures Trading and Margin Trading on MEXC</span></h3>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC also offers a futures trading tool, and MEXC makes trading derivatives seamless on its user friendly platform. Users might agree to sell or buy crypto assets at a defined price on a future date. Investors who intend to trade futures on the platform must move funds from the spot account to the derivative account to ensure stable trading.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193317 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/MEXC-futures-trading.jpg" alt="MEXC Review: Perpetual Futures Trading " width="1363" height="633" /></span></p>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">Over 1,200 futures contracts are available on MEXC, backed by industry leading liquidity. With leverage of up to 500x, these contracts allow you to control a position that is significantly larger than your initial investment. While high leverage can raise serious concerns regarding risk, the platform&#8217;s market depth supports more stable trading.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">If you&#8217;re trading USDT-M futures, you&#8217;ll use USDT as collateral. For Coin-M futures, you&#8217;ll rely on other cryptocurrencies. To ensure more stable trading, the exchange maintains industry leading liquidity. This creates an environment for stable trading, even when MEXC offers up to 200x leverage!</span></p>
<p><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/mexc-referral-code/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC perpetual futures</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> come with different order types:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trigger orders tell MEXC which price to look out for; once this price is reached, a new limit or market order is automatically placed. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A trailing stop order is a strategic order that is set when the market experiences a retracement; it basically moves with the market price. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Post-only order is a kind of limit order that doesn&#8217;t execute right away; instead, it only becomes active when it increases market liquidity.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The exchange also offers two margin modes for futures trading:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Isolated Margin Mode:</b> <span style="font-weight: 400;">This mode allows you to allocate a specific amount of your wallet balance to each position, ensuring that a loss in one doesn’t spill over and affect the others. It’s a great way to keep your risk in check.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Cross-Margin Mode</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: In this mode, your whole wallet balance is put to work supporting all your open positions. While this approach can be more efficient when it comes to margin usage, it does come with a higher risk. If one position takes a hit, it can impact your entire portfolio. </span></li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>MEXC Futures M-Day</strong></h4>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Futures M-Day is a promotional futures event in which customers trade USDT-M or Coin-M futures for a chance to win prizes in a lucky draw, mostly futures bonuses that can be used as margin, with profits available for withdrawal.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193316 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/MEXC-Futures-M-Day.jpg" alt="MEXC Futures M-Day" width="1792" height="755" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Spot traders can trade crypto futures using a variety of futures trading pairings during the Futures M-Day event. The event is intended to appeal to both experienced traders and newbies, providing an accessible and user-friendly trading environment</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<h3><strong>P2P Trading on MEXC</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With MEXC&#8217;s peer-to-peer (P2P) trading, users can easily buy and sell cryptocurrencies such as USDT, USDC, BTC, and ETH directly with each other using fiat currency. Currently, the platform supports three fiat currencies: Vietnamese Dong (VND), Russian Ruble (RUB), and South Korean Won (KRW).</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193320 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Mexc-P2P-trading.jpg" alt="P2P Trading on MEXC" width="1820" height="681" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You have the option to be an advertiser, where you can create your own ads to buy or sell, set your own fiat prices, choose your payment methods, and establish trade limits. Alternatively, you can take the role of a taker by picking an existing ad to trade with.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC uses an Escrow system as an extra layer of security. Essentially, when a trade starts, the platform places the cryptocurrency being sold in escrow until it confirms the payment. This process ensures that both the buyer and seller uphold their end of the deal.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Demo Trading</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Demo trading, as the name implies, is all about mimicking the futures trading market. It offers traders a valuable opportunity to learn by replicating real transactions. This practice is a great way to sharpen trading skills and boost overall performance.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC provides you with USDT 50,000 to begin your demo trading.Keep in mind that all demo trading activities on the simulation platform are  for practice purposes only, meaning you won&#8217;t actually make or lose any money.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Copy Trading</strong></h3>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">With MEXC&#8217;s copy trade feature, you can easily follow in the footsteps of skilled traders for your futures trading, enjoying a top tier trading experience. It is a very easy-to-use feature on the investment platform for beginners with little professional experience. Users report fast syncing of trades, which is crucial for volatile markets.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">Basically, the idea is that followers can benefit from the expertise and strategies of lead traders without the need to analyze the markets or manage every position on their own. This is enhanced by low fees and often zero fees on spot maker trades, which preserves your capital.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">To become a follower, you just need to choose a lead trader to follow and take a look at their past performance like ROI, win rate, PNL, and how often they trade. With low fees applied to transactions, you keep more profit. After that, make sure you have funds in your spot account to use as margin. Even with zero fees promotions ending, the standard low fees make MEXC a competitive choice.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You have several options for how to execute your copy trades: </span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Smart Ratio:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> This lets you copy trades based on the size of the lead trader’s orders. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Fixed Amount:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> With this option, you’ll apply the same margin amount to each trade you copy.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Fixed Ratio: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">This approach uses a multiplier of the lead trader’s order.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To get started, there&#8217;s a minimum investment required on the app or website. For instance, if you&#8217;re looking to copy trade, you&#8217;ll need to invest at least around 30 USDT for certain modes.  Lead traders benefit by earning a share of the profits from their followers&#8217; gains, and this percentage is determined ahead of time. Followers only pay this share when there&#8217;s a profit. </span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Express </strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This feature makes it super simple for users to buy cryptocurrency using payment methods they’re comfortable with, including SEPA, credit and debit cards, and various third-party payment services like MoonPay, Mercuryo, Simplex, and others. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC isn&#8217;t responsible for handling these transactions; it simply acts as a middleman between users and third-party payment providers. </span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Mastercard</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The MEXC Card is a virtual prepaid Mastercard created for MEXC exchange users. Some countries it is available in include: Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, and Switzerland.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193319 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/MEXC-Mastercard.jpg" alt="MEXC Mastercard" width="828" height="1039" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Mastercard has only one card tier which is the single card tier. To apply, make sure you&#8217;ve completed your KYC at least 14 days before submitting your application, and that you&#8217;ve made at least one previous purchase using a bank card or SEPA on MEXC.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of its features include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">0% for transactions within the European Economic Area (EEA)</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">2% for transactions outside the EEA</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seamless integration with your MEXC exchange accounts, allowing you to stay connected effortlessly. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Real-time transaction alerts right on your smartphone, so you’re always in the loop. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">3D Secure (3DS) technology, ensuring your transactions are well-protected. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No monthly fees or charges for inactivity, making it easy on your wallet. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maximum card balance of 100,000 USDT</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>MEXC Review: Staking and Earn</strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On MEXC, the term “Staking &amp; Earn” refers to features that enable users to earn rewards or interest on their crypto assets instead of just letting them sit idle.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Savings</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Savings is a product or service offered by MEXC which enables users to earn passive income on assets kept on the exchange. It is sometimes called MEXC Savings or MEXC Earn on the platform. Here, users earn yields simply by staking cryptocurrency. Yield refers to the annualized percentage return (APR) a user can earn by staking or locking up their crypto for a particular timeframe.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Currently, there are two types of MEXC Saving: “Flexible Savings” and “Locked Savings”. Users can trade, transfer and withdraw anytime in “Flexible Savings”. This type of saving is similar to the traditional banking system. Here, Users earn rewards by holding their assets in MEXC’s regular wallet. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conversely in “Locked Savings”, assets are locked for a period of time, more like a fixed deposit. Here, Users can not trade, transfer or withdraw their assets and they earn rewards.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Simply put, when MEXC says “ Earn 7% yield on USDT in Savings,” it means:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you lock $1,000 in USDT for a year, you could earn around $70 in passive income.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Loans</strong></h3>
