<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Interest accrues daily, and borrowing limits are determined by the loan-to-value (LTV) ratio. If the collateral value declines and the LTV exceeds a specified threshold, MEXC may liquidate the collateral to recover the loan. Borrowers can manage risk by adding collateral to reduce their loan-to-value ratio and prevent liquidation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-193318 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/mexc-loans-scaled.jpg" alt="mexc loans" width="2560" height="1030" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Loans offers a practical way to access liquidity while keeping long-term holdings intact, but success depends on actively managing collateral and staying aware of market risks. Therefore, it’s advised to DYOR.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Review: </strong><strong>Kickstarter and Launchpool</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Kickstarter is a pre-listing event where users vote for new projects using MX tokens. Participation is free, with tokens temporarily locked during the voting period. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rewards are distributed as airdropped project tokens. Snapshots maintain fairness, and users must complete at least one Futures trade to participate. This event increases project visibility and offers early rewards to MX holders.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conversely, MEXC Launchpool allows users to stake MX, USDT, or other tokens in designated pools to earn new project tokens proportionally. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These time-limited events often feature high APRs and substantial reward pools, such as APT. While staked tokens are locked, participants gain early access to new tokens without buying them directly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC Kickstarter and Launchpool both provide early access to new tokens, but their methods differ. Kickstarter uses MX token voting, while Launchpool requires staking and KYC verification. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Both offer low-risk exposure and rewards, though participants should be aware of potential token volatility, diluted rewards, and specific entry requirements that’s why it’s important to DYOR before diving into any project. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Together, these initiatives enhance community engagement and strengthen MEXC&#8217;s position as a platform for discovering new projects.</span></p>
<h3><strong>MEXC Review: Token Airdrop</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Airdrops on MEXC are token distributions that users can receive, often for free or as part of a rewards program, during various promotional events. These can take place through Airdrop+ events, Launchpool sessions, Kickstarter initiatives, and Initial Listings. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It&#8217;s important to note that some airdrops depend on holding MEXC’s native token, MX. For example, users may need to keep a certain amount of MX in their spot wallet for a period of time to be eligible.</span></p>
<h4><strong>How Does MEXC Token Airdrop Work</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">To get started, you&#8217;ll need to buy and hold at least 1,000 MX tokens. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep them in your spot wallet for 30 days straight while MEXC takes daily snapshots.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once those 30 days are up, just head over to MEXC Launchpad or Kickstarter, hit the commit button, and you&#8217;ll start receiving your airdrops!</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>MEXC Review: Referral and Affiliate Programs</strong></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The exchange has a referral and affiliate program that lets you earn rewards just by inviting others to join the platform. MEXC affiliate program is open to content creators with at least 500 followers, crypto websites and promotional agencies. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The first step to becoming part of their affiliate program is to submit an application. After that, you&#8217;ll need to wait for MEXC to give you the green light, and then you&#8217;ll receive a referral code. This code allows you to earn money from the trades of those you refer. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When someone signs up on the exchange using your code, they get welcome bonuses, and you earn lifetime commissions on every new active referral. Standard users get up to 40% commission on both spot and futures while affiliates get up to 70% commission. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users can also enjoy lifetime commissions on valid invitees or trades. Additional bonuses such as airdrops and VIP services may also apply. </span></p>
<h2><strong>MEXC API</strong></h2>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">The MEXC API serves as a programmatic gateway for advanced users, developers, trading bots, brokers, and institutional users to engage with MEXC&#8217;s services. This includes placing orders, checking market data for the m ost trending tokens and tradable volume, managing account balances including mx earnings, and receiving real-time updates with minimal lag.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">MEXC offers both REST endpoints and WebSocket streams to facilitate these interactions, ensuring a smooth trading experience. The platform publishes various SDKs and demo examples in several languages like Python, Java, Go, .NET, and JavaScript, making the tools accessible for both beginners and experienced traders.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-193315 aligncenter" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/MEXC-API.jpg" alt="MEXC API" width="1792" height="753" /></span></p>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span data-color="var(--green-10)">They have various API versions for Spot, Futures, and more, with the latest Spot API V3 being the preferred choice. Keep in mind that the exchange is gradually phasing out older versions.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">The exchange includes a renewal option that allows you to extend your API key for 90 days. This provides extra security assurance for algorithmic traders, as it helps lower the risk of leakage that can occur when traders submit multiple API key applications. Users looking for higher limits may need to complete advanced kyc.</span></p>
<p><span data-color="var(--green-10)">On top of that, algorithmic traders can define which trading pairs are eligible for trading with their API key. This measure is crucial in preventing market manipulation. By combining advanced kyc protocols with these features, the exchange ensures high security assurance and minimal lag for both beginners and experienced traders, ultimately enhancing the overall trading experience.</span></p>
