<h3><strong>Step 2: Complete MEXC KYC</strong></h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mexc9.jpg" alt="MEXC KYC" width="1568" height="596" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Just like many other cryptocurrency exchanges, MEXC requires you to go through a Know Your Customer (KYC) verification. This step is crucial for preventing fraud and ensuring that everyone can trade safely. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It typically involves uploading a government-issued ID or a selfie. Completing MEXC KYC gives you access to more features like increased withdrawals and bonuses. </span></p>
<h3><strong>Step 3: Deposit Funds</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC offers a range of deposit methods based on your region. For a complete list of what’s available, check out the “Buy Crypto” section on the MEXC website. You’ll typically find options like bank transfers, credit/debit card purchases (where possible), and peer-to-peer (P2P) trading.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most common deposit method is with cryptocurrency. To deposit you’ll need to:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pick the cryptocurrency you want to deposit, like BTC, USDT, or ETH. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Next, select the blockchain network that corresponds with the wallet or exchange you’re using to send your funds (for example, ERC20, TRC20, or BEP20). It is important to choose the right network because sending to the wrong one could lead to a permanent loss of your funds.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">MEXC will create a unique deposit address for you, which includes a QR code and an alphanumeric string. Make sure to copy it accurately. </span></li>
