<h3><strong>Is MEXC accessible to users in the United States?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">No. MEXC is not available for new users in the United States. Their terms clearly list the U.S. among the “Prohibited Countries/Regions.” So, even if you’ve seen the MEXC app listed in the U.S. App Store in the past, it doesn’t change the existing restrictions.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Where are MEXC headquarters?</strong></h3>
<p>MEXC’s headquarters are located in Victoria, Seychelles.</p>
<h3><strong>Can I transfer money from MEXC directly to my bank account?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you can transfer money (fiat) straight from MEXC to your bank account really depends on a few factors like your country, the level of verification on your account, and whether MEXC allows bank or fiat withdrawals in your area. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In many places, especially outside of Europe, MEXC doesn’t support direct fiat withdrawals to bank accounts. Most users have to convert their crypto to fiat on a platform that does allow bank withdrawals, or they might opt for peer-to-peer (P2P) methods instead.</span></p>
<h3><strong>Is MEXC a beginner-friendly platform?</strong></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes, MEXC is definitely beginner-friendly. Our MEXC review has demonstrated that the platform has a straightforward sign-up process, a user-friendly interface, and offers useful features like demo trading and educational resources, making it a great choice for newcomers.</span></p>
